{"id":"beor","term":"Beor","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A torch. (1.) The father of Bela, one of the kings of Edom (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 36:32\">Gen. 36:32</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The father of Balaam (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 22:5\">Num. 22:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 24:3\">24:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 24:15\">15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:8\">31:8</a>). In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Peter 2:15\">2 Pet. 2:15</a> he is called Bosor.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 36:32","Numbers 22:5","Numbers 24:3","Numbers 24:15","Numbers 31:8","2 Peter 2:15"]}